JOHANNESBURG - Three lions that have been roaming outside the Kruger National Park this week, have been killed. A SANParks spokesperson says a farmer shot and killed one after it attacked his cattle. He shot and wounded another. READ:Â Kruger lions likely driven from park by population pressure: officials SANParks then dispatched a chopper and had to shoot the wounded animal. They tracked the third lion and shot that one too. Rangers say tracks show there were only three lions, not four as has been reported. Five lions left the park in May. Four of them were recaptured. eNCA